01:04:08,460 --> 01:04:12,700
Friday, 15th July 1994

934
01:04:12,700 --> 01:04:17,509
Leytonstone and the Isle of Dogs, East London

935
01:04:17,509 --> 01:04:21,170
Emma Morley got up early on 15th July.

936
01:04:21,170 --> 01:04:25,380
Emma now lived in a rented flat in Leytonstone.

937
01:04:25,380 --> 01:04:31,279
It was quite near Cromwell Road Comprehensive
School, where she taught English and Drama.

938
01:04:31,279 --> 01:04:35,980
She had moved to the flat when she started
teaching at the school, in the autumn of the

939
01:04:35,980 --> 01:04:37,769
year before.

940
01:04:37,769 --> 01:04:43,049
Ian Whitehead spent much of his time at the
flat too.

941
01:04:43,049 --> 01:04:46,140
Emma thought she was probably in love with
Ian.

942
01:04:46,140 --> 01:04:52,859
'I am in love with him, aren't I?' she asked
herself daily.

943
01:04:52,859 --> 01:04:59,849
And every day she told herself that she was
in love with him - yes, of course she was

944
01:04:59,849 --> 01:05:00,849
in love with him.

945
01:05:00,849 --> 01:05:04,930
And her parents liked him very much, especially
her mother.

946
01:05:04,930 --> 01:05:09,009
That was important to her.

947
01:05:09,009 --> 01:05:14,589
'It's good when people's partners and mothers
get on well,' she thought.

948
01:05:14,589 --> 01:05:20,289
But Ian did take up a lot of space in the
little flat.

949
01:05:20,289 --> 01:05:24,960
But Emma had a bigger problem than the size
of her flat.

950
01:05:24,960 --> 01:05:33,130
Ian Whitehead and Dexter Mayhew - the two
men in her life - still didn't get on well.

951
01:05:33,130 --> 01:05:39,759
Dexter didn't like Emma's friendship with
Ian even though he had his own girlfriends.

952
01:05:39,759 --> 01:05:46,829
The truth was that Dexter needed Emma as an
emotional support but Ian didn't really understand

953
01:05:46,829 --> 01:05:48,380
this need.

954
01:05:48,380 --> 01:05:53,920
And Emma was especially important to Dexter
now that his mother had died.

955
01:05:53,920 --> 01:05:59,130
Ian was also very jealous of Dexter, because
he didn't want Emma to have a best friend

956
01:05:59,130 --> 01:06:02,430
who wasn't himself.

957
01:06:02,430 --> 01:06:09,369
All this was a special problem on the 15th,
because when the evening came, Emma was really

958
01:06:09,369 --> 01:06:13,480
needed in three places at once.

959
01:06:13,480 --> 01:06:17,319
Tonight was going to be Dexter's big night.

960
01:06:17,319 --> 01:06:23,230
Tonight, a new programme was going to be on
television and Dexter was one of the presenters.

961
01:06:23,230 --> 01:06:31,009
This programme - Late at Night - was a much
more important one than The Bigger Picture

962
01:06:31,009 --> 01:06:35,140
and perhaps it was going to make Dexter a
big star.

963
01:06:35,140 --> 01:06:41,930
Another of the presenters - a glamorous woman
called Suki Meadows - was already a star.

964
01:06:41,930 --> 01:06:48,680
The programme was going to be live and Dexter
wanted Emma to be at the television studio

965
01:06:48,680 --> 01:06:50,999
to support him.

966
01:06:50,999 --> 01:06:54,670
He no longer saw his other friends from university.

967
01:06:54,670 --> 01:06:57,739
He no longer wanted to see them.

968
01:06:57,739 --> 01:07:02,269
Callum O'Neill, whose computer business was
doing well, often called.

969
01:07:02,269 --> 01:07:08,769
He left messages on Dexter's answer phone
but Dexter never called him back.

970
01:07:08,769 --> 01:07:12,700
Emma was the only one of his old friends that
he cared about.

971
01:07:12,700 --> 01:07:18,210
But tonight was going to be Emma's big night
too.

972
01:07:18,210 --> 01:07:24,960
Emma was in charge of her school's end-of-year
drama production, the musical Oliver!

973
01:07:24,960 --> 01:07:27,289
And the performance was happening tonight.

974
01:07:27,289 --> 01:07:36,150
Of course this wasn't as important as Dexter's
programme, but clearly Emma had to be there.

975
01:07:36,150 --> 01:07:42,940
She'd spent many weeks preparing the children
for the show and she had to be with them.

976
01:07:42,940 --> 01:07:45,799
Tonight their parents were coming to watch
them.

977
01:07:45,799 --> 01:07:53,210
And for their parents, they were all going
to be little stars, for one night at least.

978
01:07:53,210 --> 01:07:58,200
Emma hoped it was going to make her the headmaster's
little star too.

979
01:07:58,200 --> 01:08:04,589
Her teaching career - making a difference
- was just as important as Dexter's more glamorous

980
01:08:04,589 --> 01:08:05,589
TV career, she thought.

981
01:08:05,589 --> 01:08:11,450
She knew that Dexter didn't really believe
this.

982
01:08:11,450 --> 01:08:13,420
And then there was Ian.

983
01:08:13,420 --> 01:08:16,370
Ian was feeling ill today.

984
01:08:16,370 --> 01:08:19,690
He didn't really want to go out at all tonight.

985
01:08:19,690 --> 01:08:21,950
And he didn't want her to go out.

986
01:08:21,950 --> 01:08:24,410
But she understood.

987
01:08:24,410 --> 01:08:26,590
She loved him, didn't she?

988
01:08:26,590 --> 01:08:29,060
And he was going to come to Oliver!

989
01:08:29,060 --> 01:08:30,779
Even if he still felt ill.

990
01:08:30,779 --> 01:08:33,420
He'd promised her that.

991
01:08:33,420 --> 01:08:38,920
Before leaving to go to work Emma picked up
the phone and called Dexter's number.

992
01:08:38,920 --> 01:08:40,980
She got his answerphone.

993
01:08:40,980 --> 01:08:41,980
'Hi!

994
01:08:41,980 --> 01:08:42,980
Speak to me!

995
01:08:42,980 --> 01:08:43,980
Leave me a message!'

996
01:08:43,980 --> 01:08:47,319
Dexter's 'cockney' voice said on the recording.

997
01:08:47,319 --> 01:08:51,010
So she left him a message.

998
01:08:51,010 --> 01:08:55,720
'Hi Dex, I'm sorry it's early for you,' she
said.

999
01:08:55,720 --> 01:08:57,640
'You're probably not awake yet.

1000
01:08:57,640 --> 01:09:01,390
But some of us have jobs to go to.

1001
01:09:01,390 --> 01:09:06,839
I'm sorry I won't be with you at the studio
tonight, but I want to wish you luck.

1002
01:09:06,839 --> 01:09:10,190
I know you understand that it's my big night
too.

1003
01:09:10,190 --> 01:09:11,800
That's show business, Dex!

1004
01:09:11,800 --> 01:09:14,150
I'll speak to you later.

1005
01:09:14,150 --> 01:09:16,500
Lots of love to you.

1006
01:09:16,500 --> 01:09:23,420
Oh - and Dex - you really have to change that
answer phone message.'

1007
01:09:23,420 --> 01:09:29,049
Dexter Mayhew wasn't feeling good when he
arrived at the television studio on the Isle

1008
01:09:29,049 --> 01:09:30,560
of Dogs.

1009
01:09:30,560 --> 01:09:32,339
It was his father's fault.

1010
01:09:32,339 --> 01:09:36,790
His father had left a message on his answer
phone earlier in the day.

1011
01:09:36,790 --> 01:09:41,609
'I called to wish you luck for tonight,' his
father had said.

1012
01:09:41,609 --> 01:09:43,099
'I'll be watching the programme.

1013
01:09:43,099 --> 01:09:47,589
It's so sad that your mother isn't here to
see you.

1014
01:09:47,589 --> 01:09:50,230
She was so... proud of you.

1015
01:09:50,230 --> 01:09:52,710
Well, good luck Dexter.

1016
01:09:52,710 --> 01:09:57,070
And don't take any notice of the newspapers.'

1017
01:09:57,070 --> 01:10:02,739
When he'd heard the message, Dexter had gone
out and bought all the daily newspapers.

1018
01:10:02,739 --> 01:10:07,900
He'd opened the first one at the television
pages and read the headline.

1019
01:10:07,900 --> 01:10:12,119
IS DEXTER MAYHEW THE NASTIEST MAN ON TV?

1020
01:10:12,119 --> 01:10:19,320
Dexter had drunk some vodka to settle his
nerves as he read the story beneath the headline.

1021
01:10:19,320 --> 01:10:22,210
The story wasn't kind to him.

1022
01:10:22,210 --> 01:10:29,420
Dexter was a stupid, rich boy who'd been educated
at Winchester College but pretended to be

1023
01:10:29,420 --> 01:10:33,260
a cockney, the author wrote mockingly.

1024
01:10:33,260 --> 01:10:38,700
Dexter thought that he was popular with young
people, the author said, but really young

1025
01:10:38,700 --> 01:10:40,580
people just laughed at him.

1026
01:10:40,580 --> 01:10:43,719
They didn't connect with him at all.

1027
01:10:43,719 --> 01:10:48,270
Dexter had felt sick when he read this.

1028
01:10:48,270 --> 01:10:54,150
And he had had several more drinks before
he arrived at the television studio that evening.

1029
01:10:54,150 --> 01:11:00,020
In his dressing room at the studio, Dexter
sat quietly trying to relax.

1030
01:11:00,020 --> 01:11:04,140
He had told the producer of the show that
he wanted to be alone.

1031
01:11:04,140 --> 01:11:05,980
He was nervous.

1032
01:11:05,980 --> 01:11:11,230
He had been a TV presenter for several years
now, so he was surprised at how nervous he

1033
01:11:11,230 --> 01:11:12,790
felt.

1034
01:11:12,790 --> 01:11:16,960
He didn't know what he was going to say when
the show started.

1035
01:11:16,960 --> 01:11:23,810
When he thought about the whole hour the show
was going to last, his mind was suddenly empty.

1036
01:11:23,810 --> 01:11:26,460
Now, he was very frightened.

1037
01:11:26,460 --> 01:11:30,570
And the show was going to start in a few minutes.

1038
01:11:30,570 --> 01:11:34,070
He took a bottle of vodka from his overcoat
pocket.

1039
01:11:34,070 --> 01:11:39,200
There was a bottle of water on a table in
the dressing room.

1040
01:11:39,200 --> 01:11:42,970
Presenters usually took a bottle of water
onto the set with them.

1041
01:11:42,970 --> 01:11:48,510
The studio lights were always very hot and
they often needed to drink some water when

1042
01:11:48,510 --> 01:11:49,820
they were off-camera.

1043
01:11:49,820 --> 01:11:54,380
They couldn't speak clearly if their mouths
were dry.

1044
01:11:54,380 --> 01:12:00,510
But Dexter wanted something to clear his mind,
not something to wet his mouth.

1045
01:12:00,510 --> 01:12:06,280
He emptied the water into his washbasin and
refilled the bottle with vodka.

1046
01:12:06,280 --> 01:12:09,199
Then he put it back on the table.

1047
01:12:09,199 --> 01:12:10,850
It looked the same as before.

1048
01:12:10,850 --> 01:12:13,699
Nobody would know that he was drinking vodka.

1049
01:12:13,699 --> 01:12:17,800
'HEY THERE!' said a loud voice.

1050
01:12:17,800 --> 01:12:21,219
'WELL, HOW ABOUT ALL THIS?'

1051
01:12:21,219 --> 01:12:26,090
The owner of the loud voice was Suki Meadows.

1052
01:12:26,090 --> 01:12:30,900
Suki was already a popular presenter of late-night
TV shows.

1053
01:12:30,900 --> 01:12:34,780
Now she stood at the door smiling at Dexter.

1054
01:12:34,780 --> 01:12:41,160
She was a small, pretty, friendly person and
she was always cheerful.

1055
01:12:41,160 --> 01:12:42,489
Always!

1056
01:12:42,489 --> 01:12:45,489
It didn't matter what was happening around
her.

1057
01:12:45,489 --> 01:12:47,980
She was cheerful and she was noisy.

1058
01:12:47,980 --> 01:12:53,440
'Why does Suki always speak in capital letters?'

1059
01:12:53,440 --> 01:12:55,570
Dexter had sometimes asked himself.

1060
01:12:55,570 --> 01:12:58,210
But tonight he was thinking something else.

1061
01:12:58,210 --> 01:13:01,380
'The viewers all love her.

1062
01:13:01,380 --> 01:13:05,380
And she is very sexy,' he was thinking.

1063
01:13:05,380 --> 01:13:08,070
'And I'm sure she's crazy about me.'

1064
01:13:08,070 --> 01:13:14,620
Suki was wearing a very short skirt and a
shirt made of very thin cloth.

1065
01:13:14,620 --> 01:13:17,080
And she was holding her own bottle of water.

1066
01:13:17,080 --> 01:13:22,250
'COME HERE, DEX,' she said, entering the dressing
room.

1067
01:13:22,250 --> 01:13:27,570
She put her water bottle on the table next
to his and put her arms around him.

1068
01:13:27,570 --> 01:13:30,719
'YOU'RE GOING TO BE GREAT TONIGHT!

1069
01:13:30,719 --> 01:13:32,870
WE'RE GOING TO BE GREAT TOGETHER!

1070
01:13:32,870 --> 01:13:36,520
DEX AND SUKI, SUKI AND DEX!

1071
01:13:36,520 --> 01:13:40,250
WHAT A TEAM, DEX!'

1072
01:13:40,250 --> 01:13:46,469
And having wished him good luck in her own
way, Suki led Dexter out of the dressing room.

1073
01:13:46,469 --> 01:13:49,990
On the way, they picked up their water bottles.

1074
01:13:49,990 --> 01:13:55,210
Outside, on the set, they picked up their
microphones and inserted their earpieces.

1075
01:13:55,210 --> 01:14:01,540
They looked around them at the brightly coloured
set and the brightly dressed dancers who were

1076
01:14:01,540 --> 01:14:04,969
standing ready to begin the warm up before
the show.

1077
01:14:04,969 --> 01:14:09,119
Then the music started, the dancers danced.

1078
01:14:09,119 --> 01:14:15,770
When they had finished, Suki walked to the
front of the set and yelled to the audience.

1079
01:14:15,770 --> 01:14:20,080
'ARE YOU READY TO HAVE A GREAT TIME?

1080
01:14:20,080 --> 01:14:23,020
WELL, MAKE SOME NOISE FOR US!'

1081
01:14:23,020 --> 01:14:27,070
At that moment, Dexter realized that he was
hopelessly drunk.

1082
01:14:27,070 --> 01:14:32,790
Now it was his turn to speak and he couldn't
say anything.

1083
01:14:32,790 --> 01:14:34,460
He didn't know what to say.

1084
01:14:34,460 --> 01:14:38,880
This show was going to be a disaster.

1085
01:14:38,880 --> 01:14:42,650
Someone in the audience shouted, 'You useless
idiot!

1086
01:14:42,650 --> 01:14:44,540
Can't you speak?'

1087
01:14:44,540 --> 01:14:47,060
Dexter had an idea.

1088
01:14:47,060 --> 01:14:52,620
'Well, he's clearly been reading the newspapers,'
he shouted to the audience.

1089
01:14:52,620 --> 01:14:54,690
He tried to laugh.

1090
01:14:54,690 --> 01:14:59,650
A few of the audience laughed too, but not
many of them.

1091
01:14:59,650 --> 01:15:04,590
Dexter needed another drink to clear his head,
he told himself.

1092
01:15:04,590 --> 01:15:09,239
He took the top off his water bottle and drank.

1093
01:15:09,239 --> 01:15:12,170
It was water, just water.

1094
01:15:12,170 --> 01:15:14,610
At once he understood.

1095
01:15:14,610 --> 01:15:18,480
The bottles had got mixed up.

1096
01:15:18,480 --> 01:15:21,060
Suki had the vodka.

1097
01:15:21,060 --> 01:15:23,630
And she was taking the top off her bottle.

1098
01:15:23,630 --> 01:15:28,620
He wanted to stop her drinking, but it was
too late.

1099
01:15:28,620 --> 01:15:34,810
As she tasted the liquid, Dexter saw the shock
in her eyes.

1100
01:15:34,810 --> 01:15:38,239
And at that moment, the live programme began.

1101
01:15:38,239 --> 01:15:39,520
'We're live!

1102
01:15:39,520 --> 01:15:45,960
Say something Dexter,' the producer's voice
said in his earpiece.

1103
01:15:45,960 --> 01:15:50,440
But Dexter couldn't speak and Suki was coughing.

1104
01:15:50,440 --> 01:15:53,679
She recovered first, and she came to Dexter's
rescue.

1105
01:15:53,679 --> 01:15:55,300
'SORRY ABOUT THAT.

1106
01:15:55,300 --> 01:16:02,130
BUT AT LEAST YOU VIEWERS KNOW THAT THE PROGRAMME
IS LIVE!' she said.

1107
01:16:02,130 --> 01:16:04,400
Suki went on speaking.

1108
01:16:04,400 --> 01:16:10,730
Dexter tried hard to think clearly and after
a few minutes he was able to perform better

1109
01:16:10,730 --> 01:16:11,730
with Suki.

1110
01:16:11,730 --> 01:16:16,470
He wasn't very good, but he wasn't terrible.

1111
01:16:16,470 --> 01:16:19,220
And Suki was amazing.

1112
01:16:19,220 --> 01:16:25,909
She always spoke when Dexter didn't know what
to say and she tried to make Dexter look normal.

1113
01:16:25,909 --> 01:16:30,250
The show wasn't a disaster.

1114
01:16:30,250 --> 01:16:34,489
When the programme had finished, there was
a party for all the people who had appeared

1115
01:16:34,489 --> 01:16:36,560
in it, and their friends and relations.

1116
01:16:36,560 --> 01:16:42,510
Dexter stayed for the party, but he was quiet
and thoughtful.

1117
01:16:42,510 --> 01:16:46,340
People congratulated him, but they didn't
speak to him for long.

1118
01:16:46,340 --> 01:16:53,000
He ate lots of food and drank lots of wine,
but he wasn't happy.

1119
01:16:53,000 --> 01:16:56,500
He knew that he hadn't performed well.

1120
01:16:56,500 --> 01:17:00,250
He knew that Suki Meadows had rescued him.

1121
01:17:00,250 --> 01:17:04,740
And he knew that she had been the star.

1122
01:17:04,740 --> 01:17:08,140
Late in the evening, Suki came to sit next
to him.

1123
01:17:08,140 --> 01:17:11,050
'That went OK, didn't it?'

1124
01:17:11,050 --> 01:17:12,050
she said.

1125
01:17:12,050 --> 01:17:16,750
For the first time that day, she wasn't speaking
in capital letters.

1126
01:17:16,750 --> 01:17:19,980
'You saved us, Suki,' he said.

1127
01:17:19,980 --> 01:17:25,030
'I was trying to settle my nerves, but I drank
too much before the show.

1128
01:17:25,030 --> 01:17:27,510
I owe you an apology.'

1129
01:17:27,510 --> 01:17:30,840
'Yes, you do,' she replied.

1130
01:17:30,840 --> 01:17:35,770
'You have a problem with alcohol and we need
to talk about it.

1131
01:17:35,770 --> 01:17:41,349
You must understand this, Dexter - you won't
appear on this programme with me again if

1132
01:17:41,349 --> 01:17:42,349
you aren't sober.

1133
01:17:42,349 --> 01:17:46,250
And you must never bring alcohol onto the
set again.'

1134
01:17:46,250 --> 01:17:51,770
'What can I do to make you feel better about
me?'

1135
01:17:51,770 --> 01:17:53,850
Dexter asked her.

1136
01:17:53,850 --> 01:17:59,710
'Well, you can take me out for dinner next
week,' Suki said.

1137
01:17:59,710 --> 01:18:02,280
'Take me somewhere very expensive.

1138
01:18:02,280 --> 01:18:03,550
On Tuesday.'

1139
01:18:03,550 --> 01:18:06,730
Dexter thought for a moment.

1140
01:18:06,730 --> 01:18:13,040
He had promised to meet Emma on Tuesday evening,
but he could change that.

1141
01:18:13,040 --> 01:18:15,119
Emma was his best friend.

1142
01:18:15,119 --> 01:18:17,360
She was always there for him.

1143
01:18:17,360 --> 01:18:21,080
'All right,' he replied.

1144
01:18:21,080 --> 01:18:23,469
'We have a date.'

1145
01:18:23,469 --> 01:18:25,120
'Good,' said Suki, kissing him.

1146
01:18:25,120 --> 01:18:27,909
'And now, you must come and meet my mother.'

1147
01:18:27,909 --> 01:18:37,020
Dexter was feeling a bit unhappy on the Isle
of Dogs, but Emma was on top of the world

1148
01:18:37,020 --> 01:18:38,100
in Leytonstone.

1149
01:18:38,100 --> 01:18:40,360
Oliver had been a great success.

1150
01:18:40,360 --> 01:18:46,679
Of course there had been arguments and fights
among the children before the show.

1151
01:18:46,679 --> 01:18:48,000
That always happened.

1152
01:18:48,000 --> 01:18:51,990
They were excited and some of them were nervous.

1153
01:18:51,990 --> 01:18:58,449
But Emma had settled their nerves and when
the music began, they all worked together

1154
01:18:58,449 --> 01:19:00,030
and helped each other.

1155
01:19:00,030 --> 01:19:03,780
So the show had been wonderful.

1156
01:19:03,780 --> 01:19:08,840
Phil Godaiming, Emma's headteacher, was very
pleased.

1157
01:19:08,840 --> 01:19:13,239
People whose children could act and sing like
that were going to be proud, he thought.

1158
01:19:13,239 --> 01:19:20,160
They were going to speak well of the school
- and of its headteacher, of course.

1159
01:19:20,160 --> 01:19:26,230
At the party after the show the school staff,
and many of the proud parents of the cast,

1160
01:19:26,230 --> 01:19:28,630
congratulated Emma.

1161
01:19:28,630 --> 01:19:31,270
She drank her wine and smiled at everyone.

1162
01:19:31,270 --> 01:19:36,679
And late in the evening, Mr Godaiming came
to sit next to her.

1163
01:19:36,679 --> 01:19:41,949
'You're a wonderful teacher, Emma,' he said
quietly in her ear.

1164
01:19:41,949 --> 01:19:44,949
'And you look very beautiful tonight.

1165
01:19:44,949 --> 01:20:00,170
I have great plans for you next year.'

1166
01:20:00,170 --> 01:20:01,869
CHAPTER EIGHT
A Crisis

1167
01:20:01,869 --> 01:20:06,860
Saturday, 15th July 1995

1168
01:20:06,860 --> 01:20:11,949
Walthamstow, East London and Soho, Central
London

1169
01:20:11,949 --> 01:20:15,760
'I'm going out now, Ian,' Emma called.

1170
01:20:15,760 --> 01:20:21,640
Then she added carefully, 'Are you sure that
you don't want to come with me, darling?

1171
01:20:21,640 --> 01:20:26,790
Dexter will be pleased to see you, if you
do come.'

1172
01:20:26,790 --> 01:20:29,010
'No, I can't come tonight.'

1173
01:20:29,010 --> 01:20:31,639
Ian replied, entering the room.

1174
01:20:31,639 --> 01:20:35,070
'I've got things to do tonight, don't you
remember?

1175
01:20:35,070 --> 01:20:36,560
I'm performing at the House of Ha Ha.

1176
01:20:36,560 --> 01:20:38,389
You go on your own.

1177
01:20:38,389 --> 01:20:39,570
I'll be fine.'

1178
01:20:39,570 --> 01:20:42,739
This was the right answer, Emma thought.

1179
01:20:42,739 --> 01:20:47,110
She was quite glad that she was going to see
Dexter alone.

1180
01:20:47,110 --> 01:20:52,639
She wanted to talk to him about her relationship
with Ian Whitehead.

1181
01:20:52,639 --> 01:20:57,750
Emma was beginning to understand that she
had made a bad mistake about Ian.

1182
01:20:57,750 --> 01:21:02,420
They were living together now in a flat in
Walthamstow.

1183
01:21:02,420 --> 01:21:04,929
They had bought the flat together.

1184
01:21:04,929 --> 01:21:08,520
And that was the mistake.

1185
01:21:08,520 --> 01:21:12,310
Ian loved her very much, Emma knew this.

1186
01:21:12,310 --> 01:21:17,639
And she had told herself often that she really
loved him too and that she wanted to spend

1187
01:21:17,639 --> 01:21:19,770
her life with him.

1188
01:21:19,770 --> 01:21:22,770
But she now knew that it wasn't true.

1189
01:21:22,770 --> 01:21:25,639
She was no longer happy with Ian.

1190
01:21:25,639 --> 01:21:28,670
She just didn't love him.

1191
01:21:28,670 --> 01:21:34,639
She knew that Ian hated the success of her
career and that he hated the failure of his

1192
01:21:34,639 --> 01:21:35,730
own career.

1193
01:21:35,730 --> 01:21:42,179
He still wanted desperately to be a stand-up
comedian, but he only ever performed at pubs

1194
01:21:42,179 --> 01:21:44,099
and small comedy clubs.

1195
01:21:44,099 --> 01:21:50,929
Ian just wasn't very good at stand-up and
he didn't earn much money from it.

1196
01:21:50,929 --> 01:21:54,130
Emma was feeling trapped.

1197
01:21:54,130 --> 01:21:57,800
So she needed Dexter to understand.

1198
01:21:57,800 --> 01:22:01,929
She hoped it was going to be possible to talk
sensibly to him tonight.

1199
01:22:01,929 --> 01:22:06,329
She was feeling a little nervous about

1200
01:22:06,329 --> 01:22:07,329
that.

1201
01:22:07,329 --> 01:22:11,070
Perhaps talking about Ian wasn't going to
be easy.

1202
01:22:11,070 --> 01:22:15,030
In the past, it had been easy to talk to Dexter.

1203
01:22:15,030 --> 01:22:17,610
But now he had changed.

1204
01:22:17,610 --> 01:22:21,969
He drank far too much and he was more careless
than ever about people's feelings.

1205
01:22:21,969 --> 01:22:27,550
Ian wasn't Emma's only problem of course.

1206
01:22:27,550 --> 01:22:31,090
She was no longer enjoying her job much either.

1207
01:22:31,090 --> 01:22:33,469
She was a good teacher, she knew that.

1208
01:22:33,469 --> 01:22:38,590
But she got tired and she didn't have much
time to write.

1209
01:22:38,590 --> 01:22:44,590
She still wanted to be a writer, but when
she did write, the results were never very

1210
01:22:44,590 --> 01:22:45,590
good.

1211
01:22:45,590 --> 01:22:49,840
That was as bad a problem as her relationship
with Ian.

1212
01:22:49,840 --> 01:22:56,500
But the greatest problem for Emma was that
she knew, in her heart, that Dexter Mayhew

1213
01:22:56,500 --> 01:23:00,140
was the person she really loved.

1214
01:23:00,140 --> 01:23:02,579
So there it was.

1215
01:23:02,579 --> 01:23:05,619
Everything was a bit hopeless.

1216
01:23:05,619 --> 01:23:12,150
Ian's career wasn't what he'd hoped for and
her career wasn't what she'd hoped for.

1217
01:23:12,150 --> 01:23:16,960
She had a feeling that Dexter's career wasn't
quite what he'd hoped for either.

1218
01:23:16,960 --> 01:23:21,199
Suki Meadows was his girlfriend these days.

1219
01:23:21,199 --> 01:23:25,810
But she was now clearly the star presenter
of Late at Night.

1220
01:23:25,810 --> 01:23:29,290
Dex was definitely the number two person.

1221
01:23:29,290 --> 01:23:32,860
He wasn't very popular with the audience.

1222
01:23:32,860 --> 01:23:38,989
And nasty people often wrote cruel things
about him in the newspapers now.

1223
01:23:38,989 --> 01:23:44,630
Emma and Dexter were meeting for dinner at
an expensive restaurant in Soho.

1224
01:23:44,630 --> 01:23:51,110
It was the kind of place where fashionable
people ate - people in television, like Dexter

1225
01:23:51,110 --> 01:23:53,360
and Suki Meadows.

1226
01:23:53,360 --> 01:23:56,940
Emma hoped she was going to like it.

1227
01:23:56,940 --> 01:24:00,000
Dexter was waiting for Emma outside the restaurant.

1228
01:24:00,000 --> 01:24:03,840
He was talking on his mobile phone.

1229
01:24:03,840 --> 01:24:07,739
Emma heard his caller's voice quite clearly
as she arrived.

1230
01:24:07,739 --> 01:24:11,620
'TEN MILLION VIEWERS THIS WEEK, DEX!'

1231
01:24:11,620 --> 01:24:14,860
the voice said, very loudly.

1232
01:24:14,860 --> 01:24:17,180
'TEN MILLION!'

1233
01:24:17,180 --> 01:24:24,050
'Suki, let me explain something about telephones,'
Dex replied into the phone.

1234
01:24:24,050 --> 01:24:27,760
'You don't need to shout into them.

1235
01:24:27,760 --> 01:24:30,000
The phone does the shouting for you.

1236
01:24:30,000 --> 01:24:33,540
I have to go now,' he added when he saw Emma.

1237
01:24:33,540 --> 01:24:35,829
'I'll see you soon.'

1238
01:24:35,829 --> 01:24:42,600
'Dex, those things are so stupid,' Emma said,
pointing at Dexter's phone.

1239
01:24:42,600 --> 01:24:46,130
'Why don't you throw it away?'

1240
01:24:46,130 --> 01:24:51,369
'You'll have one in less than six months,'
Dexter replied, kissing her.

1241
01:24:51,369 --> 01:24:52,460
'You'll see.

1242
01:24:52,460 --> 01:24:54,000
I'm right.'

1243
01:24:54,000 --> 01:24:59,550
They went inside the restaurant and sat at
the bar where Dexter bought drinks.

1244
01:24:59,550 --> 01:25:04,179
After a few minutes, they heard a soft, female
voice behind them.

1245
01:25:04,179 --> 01:25:06,880
'Do you want cigarettes, sir?'

1246
01:25:06,880 --> 01:25:08,380
the voice said.

1247
01:25:08,380 --> 01:25:14,190
They turned to see a very tall, extraordinarily
beautiful girl.

1248
01:25:14,190 --> 01:25:21,340
The girl was dressed only in black underwear
and stockings, and she carried a tray containing

1249
01:25:21,340 --> 01:25:23,170
the cigarettes.

1250
01:25:23,170 --> 01:25:25,530
She had a fixed smile.

1251
01:25:25,530 --> 01:25:27,969
It wasn't a happy smile.

1252
01:25:27,969 --> 01:25:30,460
Dexter bought some cigarettes.

1253
01:25:30,460 --> 01:25:37,000
He spent a long time finding his money, so
that he could look at the girl's body.

1254
01:25:37,000 --> 01:25:39,090
Then the girl moved away.

1255
01:25:39,090 --> 01:25:43,380
'Why is she dressed like that, Dexter?'

1256
01:25:43,380 --> 01:25:44,599
Emma said.

1257
01:25:44,599 --> 01:25:48,510
'I don't know, Em,' Dexter replied.

1258
01:25:48,510 --> 01:25:51,650
'Perhaps all her ugly clothes are in the laundry.

1259
01:25:51,650 --> 01:25:53,500
You could look like that if you wanted,' he
added.

1260
01:25:53,500 --> 01:25:56,460
'You've got a great body.'

1261
01:25:56,460 --> 01:26:02,329
'But I don't want to look like that,' said
Emma.

1262
01:26:02,329 --> 01:26:04,860
Soon a waiter took them to their table.

1263
01:26:04,860 --> 01:26:08,880
They ordered drinks and when those arrived,
they ordered food.

1264
01:26:08,880 --> 01:26:11,579
Dexter was drinking quickly.

1265
01:26:11,579 --> 01:26:16,699
'And soon he'll be drunk - again,' Emma told
herself.

1266
01:26:16,699 --> 01:26:20,389
And she couldn't stop thinking about the cigarette
girl.

1267
01:26:20,389 --> 01:26:27,750
'Why am I eating in the kind of restaurant
where girls have to dress like that?'

1268
01:26:27,750 --> 01:26:29,180
she asked herself.

1269
01:26:29,180 --> 01:26:32,719
Then she asked Dexter the same question.

1270
01:26:32,719 --> 01:26:36,869
'This place is terrible, Dex,' Emma said.

1271
01:26:36,869 --> 01:26:42,130
'Haven't women made any progress in the last
hundred years?'

1272
01:26:42,130 --> 01:26:45,760
'You don't understand, Em,' Dexter said.

1273
01:26:45,760 --> 01:26:50,000
'Dressing like that gives her power over men.

1274
01:26:50,000 --> 01:26:51,000
She enjoys it.'

1275
01:26:51,000 --> 01:26:53,260
'Don't be stupid, Dexter,' Emma said.

1276
01:26:53,260 --> 01:26:57,180
'The owner of this place makes her wear those
clothes.

1277
01:26:57,180 --> 01:27:00,710
If she doesn't wear them, she'll lose her
job.

1278
01:27:00,710 --> 01:27:06,469
She only works here because she needs the
money, you can see that.

1279
01:27:06,469 --> 01:27:09,920
She has no power over anyone!'

1280
01:27:09,920 --> 01:27:14,170
'Well, you're still the same old Emma, aren't
you?'

1281
01:27:14,170 --> 01:27:15,770
Dexter said crossly.

1282
01:27:15,770 --> 01:27:18,420
'Emma, the angry, socialist feminist.

1283
01:27:18,420 --> 01:27:22,770
I thought that you'd mellowed, but clearly
I was wrong about that.

1284
01:27:22,770 --> 01:27:25,520
You never want to compromise, do you?'

1285
01:27:25,520 --> 01:27:29,590
After that, the evening got worse and worse.

1286
01:27:29,590 --> 01:27:33,570
Dexter frequently left the table to visit
the toilet.

1287
01:27:33,570 --> 01:27:36,690
Each time, he stopped to talk to the cigarette
girl.

1288
01:27:36,690 --> 01:27:43,389
The last time it happened, Emma saw him push
a piece of paper into her stocking.

1289
01:27:43,389 --> 01:27:47,110
Emma had no doubt that he was giving the girl
his phone number.

1290
01:27:47,110 --> 01:27:53,960
When he returned to the table, Emma decided
she had had enough of his behaviour.

1291
01:27:53,960 --> 01:27:59,880
She pushed the table away from her, spilling
their drinks, and ran up the stairs out of

1292
01:27:59,880 --> 01:28:01,530
the restaurant.

1293
01:28:01,530 --> 01:28:05,449
She could hear Dexter behind her, calling
her name.

1294
01:28:05,449 --> 01:28:07,929
She didn't turn round.

1295
01:28:07,929 --> 01:28:11,139
In the street, Dexter finally caught up with
her.

1296
01:28:11,139 --> 01:28:14,750
'Emma, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

1297
01:28:14,750 --> 01:28:18,920
I didn't mean to upset you,' he said desperately.

1298
01:28:18,920 --> 01:28:21,329
Suddenly, Emma turned to face him.

1299
01:28:21,329 --> 01:28:27,429
'Dexter, whenever I see you now you're drunk,'
she said.

1300
01:28:27,429 --> 01:28:30,840
'I haven't seen you sober for three years.

1301
01:28:30,840 --> 01:28:33,599
I don't know you any longer.

1302
01:28:33,599 --> 01:28:36,080
You're obnoxious these days.

1303
01:28:36,080 --> 01:28:41,520
You were always a bit obnoxious, but now you're
totally obnoxious.'

1304
01:28:41,520 --> 01:28:45,989
'I'm just having fun, Emma,' Dexter replied.

1305
01:28:45,989 --> 01:28:50,119
'Well, it isn't fun for me,' Emma replied.

1306
01:28:50,119 --> 01:28:52,699
'Let's stop this now, Dexter.

1307
01:28:52,699 --> 01:28:54,829
You don't care about me.

1308
01:28:54,829 --> 01:28:57,900
We don't have to meet any more.'

1309
01:28:57,900 --> 01:29:01,790
'Emma, of course we have to meet,' Dexter
said desperately.

1310
01:29:01,790 --> 01:29:04,480
'We're Dex and Em, aren't we?

1311
01:29:04,480 --> 01:29:07,699
We'll always be Dex and Em.'

1312
01:29:07,699 --> 01:29:10,250
For a moment he was quiet.

1313
01:29:10,250 --> 01:29:14,010
He was thinking of the day of his mother's
funeral.

1314
01:29:14,010 --> 01:29:18,280
He was thinking of Emma's kindness to him
that day.

1315
01:29:18,280 --> 01:29:22,349
She had held him as he cried uncontrollably.

1316
01:29:22,349 --> 01:29:26,219
He had always taken her for granted, he knew
that.

1317
01:29:26,219 --> 01:29:31,540
'Why am I throwing all this away?' he was
asking himself.

1318
01:29:31,540 --> 01:29:34,510
But he knew that he couldn't stop himself.

1319
01:29:34,510 --> 01:29:38,070
'Dexter,' Emma said sadly.

1320
01:29:38,070 --> 01:29:44,800
'I love you very much and I probably always
will love you.

1321
01:29:44,800 --> 01:29:49,340
But I'm afraid I don't like you any longer.

1322
01:29:49,340 --> 01:29:53,989
I don't like the person that you've become.

1323
01:29:53,989 --> 01:29:56,170
I don't want to hear from you again.

1324
01:29:56,170 --> 01:30:00,360
Please don't try to contact me.'

1325
01:30:00,360 --> 01:30:05,980
She left him standing in the street and walked
away.

1326
01:30:05,980 --> 01:30:16,600
CHAPTER NINE
Things End

1327
01:30:16,600 --> 01:30:27,220
Monday, 15th July 1996

1328
01:30:27,220 --> 01:30:33,190
Leytonstone and Walthamstow, East London

1329
01:30:33,190 --> 01:30:36,760
At six o'clock on the last day of term at
Cromwell Road lx.

1330
01:30:36,760 --> 01:30:41,400
Comprehensive School, almost everyone had
gone home.

1331
01:30:41,400 --> 01:30:47,550
Only Emma Morley and Mr Godaiming, the school's
headteacher, were still in the building.

1332
01:30:47,550 --> 01:30:52,260
They were lying on the floor of Mr Godaiming's
office.

1333
01:30:52,260 --> 01:31:00,300
'I'll miss you very much during the holidays,
Emma,' Mr Godaiming said as they put on their

1334
01:31:00,300 --> 01:31:01,300
clothes.

1335
01:31:01,300 --> 01:31:02,790
'I'll miss our Friday afternoons together.'

1336
01:31:02,790 --> 01:31:09,449
'No you won't, Phil, you'll have Mrs Godaiming,'
Emma replied unkindly.

1337
01:31:09,449 --> 01:31:12,340
'You'll be fine.'

1338
01:31:12,340 --> 01:31:17,770
Emma wondered, as she spoke, why she always
felt so cross after their meetings in the

1339
01:31:17,770 --> 01:31:19,210
headteacher's office.

1340
01:31:19,210 --> 01:31:23,780
Afterwards she always felt unhappy and that
made her cross.

1341
01:31:23,780 --> 01:31:28,909
They collected their coats and books and the
headteacher locked the office.

1342
01:31:28,909 --> 01:31:35,239
As they walked to the school car park, Emma
was thinking hard.

1343
01:31:35,239 --> 01:31:40,820
She had been Phil Godaiming's lover for nine
months now and she was starting to worry about

1344
01:31:40,820 --> 01:31:41,820
this.

1345
01:31:41,820 --> 01:31:48,139
She was afraid that he was going to tell his
wife about their relationship and ask for

1346
01:31:48,139 --> 01:31:49,280
a divorce.

1347
01:31:49,280 --> 01:31:51,989
That was not what Emma wanted at all.

1348
01:31:51,989 --> 01:31:54,760
She didn't love Phil.

1349
01:31:54,760 --> 01:31:56,469
She had never really loved him.

1350
01:31:56,469 --> 01:32:02,060
For a short time, he had made her feel better
when her life had become very sad.

1351
01:32:02,060 --> 01:32:06,610
She wasn't seeing Dexter any longer and she
missed him.

1352
01:32:06,610 --> 01:32:10,760
And her relationship with Ian Whitehead had
gone wrong.

1353
01:32:10,760 --> 01:32:14,730
Phil had helped her to be confident during
the bad times.

1354
01:32:14,730 --> 01:32:18,290
But she certainly didn't want to marry him.

1355
01:32:18,290 --> 01:32:22,280
And she thought now that it was time for this
relationship to end.

1356
01:32:22,280 --> 01:32:28,810
As Mr Godaiming opened the door of his car,
Emma held his arm.

1357
01:32:28,810 --> 01:32:35,850
'Phil, I'm sorry but I don't want to be your
lover any longer,' she said.

1358
01:32:35,850 --> 01:32:37,719
'I feel bad about our relationship.

1359
01:32:37,719 --> 01:32:39,730
I feel bad about your wife.

1360
01:32:39,730 --> 01:32:41,679
I'm not happy.'

1361
01:32:41,679 --> 01:32:47,570
'You were very happy ten minutes ago, Emma,'
the headteacher said.

1362
01:32:47,570 --> 01:32:48,670
He laughed.

1363
01:32:48,670 --> 01:32:55,650
'No, Phil, you were very happy ten minutes
ago,' Emma replied sadly.

1364
01:32:55,650 --> 01:33:00,060
Phil Godaiming wasn't pleased to hear Emma's
words.

1365
01:33:00,060 --> 01:33:04,530
He'd enjoyed their meetings after school on
Fridays.

1366
01:33:04,530 --> 01:33:09,770
He argued for some time, but clearly, Emma
wasn't going to change her mind.

1367
01:33:09,770 --> 01:33:14,380
'We'll talk about this next term,' he said.

1368
01:33:14,380 --> 01:33:20,070
He got into his car, closed the door and drove
quickly out of the car park.

1369
01:33:20,070 --> 01:33:24,880
Emma travelled sadly home to Walthamstow on
the Underground.

1370
01:33:24,880 --> 01:33:29,390
On her way home, she bought some wine to drink
later.

1371
01:33:29,390 --> 01:33:32,680
She was going to spend the evening on her
own.

1372
01:33:32,680 --> 01:33:35,560
Ian Whitehead no longer lived with her.

1373
01:33:35,560 --> 01:33:40,210
They had ended their relationship after a
terrible argument.

1374
01:33:40,210 --> 01:33:45,040
They had argued about Ian's jealousy and his
selfishness.

1375
01:33:45,040 --> 01:33:48,969
At the end of their argument they had both
cried.

1376
01:33:48,969 --> 01:33:52,460
They had cried for each other and for the
end of their relationship.

1377
01:33:52,460 --> 01:33:55,540
But they both knew that it had to end.

1378
01:33:55,540 --> 01:34:03,050
It had all been so sad, Emma thought now,
as she sat in the train.

1379
01:34:03,050 --> 01:34:07,210
Late that evening, after she had drunk the
wine, Emma turned on her television.

1380
01:34:07,210 --> 01:34:12,320
The first person she saw was Dexter Mayhew.

1381
01:34:12,320 --> 01:34:18,370
Suddenly, Emma realized that it was exactly
a year since she had spoken to him.

1382
01:34:18,370 --> 01:34:23,210
She knew that Dexter's TV career hadn't been
very successful recently.

1383
01:34:23,210 --> 01:34:27,360
Viewers had never really loved him, it seemed.

1384
01:34:27,360 --> 01:34:30,370
They had only loved to hate him.

1385
01:34:30,370 --> 01:34:34,020
And nowadays most of them just hated him.

1386
01:34:34,020 --> 01:34:40,099
Dexter was now presenting a very late-night
TV show about computer games.

1387
01:34:40,099 --> 01:34:43,260
Few people watched it.

1388
01:34:43,260 --> 01:34:45,960
Emma did watch the show for a few minutes.

1389
01:34:45,960 --> 01:34:48,940
She thought that Dexter wasn't looking well.

1390
01:34:48,940 --> 01:34:54,179
His face was looking tired and he no longer
seemed confident.

1391
01:34:54,179 --> 01:34:59,429
Suddenly, Emma had a great feeling of friendship
and love for him.

1392
01:34:59,429 --> 01:35:06,250
She realized that for the last eight years,
she had thought about Dexter every day.

1393
01:35:06,250 --> 01:35:09,349
Now she knew that she wanted his friendship
again.

1394
01:35:09,349 --> 01:35:14,010
She wanted him to be her best friend again.

1395
01:35:14,010 --> 01:35:16,820
'I'll call him tomorrow,' she told herself.

1396
01:35:16,820 --> 01:35:21,380
'I really will call him.'

1397
01:35:21,380 --> 01:35:29,440
CHAPTER TEN
Resignation

1398
01:35:29,440 --> 01:35:40,190
Tuesday, 15th July 1997

