01:51:38,671 --> 01:51:39,671
Saturday, 15th July 2006

2110
01:51:39,671 --> 01:51:40,671
London, England

2111
01:51:40,671 --> 01:51:41,671
The months had passed.

2112
01:51:41,671 --> 01:51:42,671
Another year had passed.

2113
01:51:42,671 --> 01:51:43,671
For Dexter, the second anniversary of Emma's
death wasn't as painful as the first one.

2114
01:51:43,671 --> 01:51:44,671
When the deli closed for the day, he decided
to spend the evening alone.

2115
01:51:44,671 --> 01:51:45,671
He wanted to look through Emma's books and
photographs.

2116
01:51:45,671 --> 01:51:46,671
He was going to keep some of them.

2117
01:51:46,671 --> 01:51:47,671
He was going to give some of them to her parents.

2118
01:51:47,671 --> 01:51:48,671
The others were going to her friends.

2119
01:51:48,671 --> 01:51:49,671
So in the evening, he sat with Emma's things
around him.

2120
01:51:49,671 --> 01:51:50,671
He thought about the previous anniversary
and he remembered a strange thing.

2121
01:51:50,671 --> 01:51:51,671
A few days after 15th July last year, he'd
received a kind letter from Ian Whitehead.

2122
01:51:51,671 --> 01:51:52,671
'When Emma left me, I hated you,' he had written.

2123
01:51:52,671 --> 01:51:53,671
'I wanted to die.

2124
01:51:53,671 --> 01:51:54,671
But after a few years I met someone else and
my life changed.

2125
01:51:54,671 --> 01:51:55,671
And now I'm happy again.

2126
01:51:55,671 --> 01:51:56,671
We have three children.

2127
01:51:56,671 --> 01:51:57,671
I know how you must feel without Emma, Dexter.

2128
01:51:57,671 --> 01:51:58,671
And I know that she loved you very, very much.

2129
01:51:58,671 --> 01:51:59,671
I used to think that you weren't good enough
for her.

2130
01:51:59,671 --> 01:52:00,671
But none of us was good enough for Emma.

2131
01:52:00,671 --> 01:52:01,671
And we have to go on for her.

2132
01:52:01,671 --> 01:52:02,671
Please take care of yourself.'

2133
01:52:02,671 --> 01:52:03,671
After that letter, Dexter and Ian had spoken
on the phone a few times.

2134
01:52:03,671 --> 01:52:04,671
But they both knew that they weren't going
to meet again.

2135
01:52:04,671 --> 01:52:05,671
Dexter spent a lot of the evening looking
at Emma's old photos.

2136
01:52:05,671 --> 01:52:06,671
He found some which Emma had taken on Arthur's

2137
01:52:06,671 --> 01:52:07,671
Seat in Edinburgh.

2138
01:52:07,671 --> 01:52:08,671
One of them had been taken by someone else
and showed both Emma and Dexter.

2139
01:52:08,671 --> 01:52:09,671
These photos had been taken on the first day
they had ever spent together.

2140
01:52:09,671 --> 01:52:10,671
Suddenly, Dexter felt terrible.

2141
01:52:10,671 --> 01:52:11,671
There were so many memories.

2142
01:52:11,671 --> 01:52:12,671
He started to cry, but he knew what to do.

2143
01:52:12,671 --> 01:52:13,671
He phoned his friend Maddy.

2144
01:52:13,671 --> 01:52:14,671
Talking to her made him calm again.

2145
01:52:14,671 --> 01:52:15,671
'Shall I come to you?'

2146
01:52:15,671 --> 01:52:16,671
she said.

2147
01:52:16,671 --> 01:52:17,671
'I can get a taxi.'

2148
01:52:17,671 --> 01:52:18,671
'No, it's all right.

2149
01:52:18,671 --> 01:52:19,671
I just wanted hear a friendly voice,' Dexter
told her.

2150
01:52:19,671 --> 01:52:20,671
'I'll be fine now.'

2151
01:52:20,671 --> 01:52:21,671
And soon, he felt much better.

