2165
01:52:34,671 --> 01:52:35,671
of the flat where Emma used to live.

2166
01:52:35,671 --> 01:52:36,671
Then they walked through the streets towards
Arthur's Seat.

2167
01:52:36,671 --> 01:52:37,671
'Let's do some climbing,' said Dexter when
they reached the hill.

2168
01:52:37,671 --> 01:52:38,671
'There's a wonderful view from the top.'

2169
01:52:38,671 --> 01:52:39,671
'Did Emma come up here too?'

2170
01:52:39,671 --> 01:52:40,671
Jasmine asked him when they reached the top.

2171
01:52:40,671 --> 01:52:41,671
'Yes, we came here together,' Dexter replied.

2172
01:52:41,671 --> 01:52:42,671
'I have a photo of us both on the hill.

2173
01:52:42,671 --> 01:52:43,671
I'll show you it when we get back to London.'

2174
01:52:43,671 --> 01:52:44,671
'Do you miss Emma?'

2175
01:52:44,671 --> 01:52:45,671
Jasmine asked quietly.

2176
01:52:45,671 --> 01:52:46,671
'Yes, I miss her every day,' Dexter said.

2177
01:52:46,671 --> 01:52:47,671
'She was my best friend.

2178
01:52:47,671 --> 01:52:48,671
Do you miss her?'

2179
01:52:48,671 --> 01:52:49,671
'I think I miss her,' Jasmine said.

2180
01:52:49,671 --> 01:52:50,671
'But I was only four when she died.

2181
01:52:50,671 --> 01:52:51,671
I don't remember her very well.

2182
01:52:51,671 --> 01:52:52,671
She was nice, wasn't she?'

2183
01:52:52,671 --> 01:52:53,671
'She was very nice,' Dexter said.

2184
01:52:53,671 --> 01:52:54,671
'Who's your best friend now, Daddy?'

2185
01:52:54,671 --> 01:52:55,671
asked Jasmine.

2186
01:52:55,671 --> 01:52:56,671
'You are, of course,' Dexter replied quickly.

